<br>
What she said.<br>
<br>
Best way to go about it, I think is to take note of the people you see around you and who you group with from day to day.  Luckily, we all wear our guild affliliations on our sleeve (or over our heads, as the case may be) so you can start to make judgements based on that.<br>
<br>
Like minded people tend to stick together, so if you start to notice a trend that &quot;Mitzi's Muffinmen&quot; are all a bunch of agreeable lads, the perhaps you should ask to speak to an officer to learn more.  On the flip side, if you start noticing that &quot;The Order of Obnoxious Arrogance&quot; is living up to it's name....<br>
<br>
The only drawback to this approach that I can see is that it is difficult to find a comprehensive list of guild sites that is easily searchable.  I know before I as invited to the Troupe, I wanted to find out more about some of the Guilds that I saw around (Kelethin Legion, Elven Blades, etc.) - IN SECRET, you see? - but was stymied by my inability to find out where they set up their guild tent.<br>
<br>
BUT - it does add a whole new layer of social interaction into the game, and I think that it is something that can really be worth the effort.  So, short story made long.... what Kimaya said.<br>
